Implement minor code refactoring across various modules
This commit includes a series of minor code refactoring and updates across various modules as needed to improve overall code quality. The changes predominantly include cleaning up the spacing and indentation, modifying several function logic such as changing boolean and array values, removing and adding functions, and updating test queries for more accurate testing. Note that no major functionality was updated or added.

Refactor code for readability and correctness
The codebase underwent a range of minor adjustments to improve consistency and alignment of the code. Updates also improved the boolean logic in certain functions, added new functionality for fetching boolean values, and enhanced the test scenarios for better code coverage. These changes were primarily focused on maintaining the code's quality standards.

Add new options to clap flags in options.rs
New command line options, 'pe_chunk' and 'att_chunk', have been added to the options.rs file. These modifications improve the flexibility and customizability of the program by allowing the user to input the values for these two new options. The user's experience and the program's functionality have been enhanced with this update.

Implement parse_to_i32_vec function and update attribute types in JSON
Introduced a parse_to_i32_vec function in the helper module and modified attribute types from STRING to INTEGER in the all_attr_info.json file. The new function expands the parsing capabilities of the application. The modifications to the JSON file ensure the correct data types are used for default values, fostering data consistency and integrity.

Change attribute types from STRING to INTEGER in JSON
Updated the "default_val" and "att_type" fields in the 'all_attr_info.json' from STRING to INTEGER. This change ensures the correct data types are used for default values, improving data consistency and reliability across the application.
